SIMPLE: milesian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Milesian
<hw>Mi*le"sian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Milesius</ets>, Gr. <?/.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anc. Geog.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to Miletus,
a city of Asia Minor, or to its inhabitants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Irish Legendary Hist.)</fld> <def>Descended from
King Milesius of Spain, whose two sons are said to have conquered
Ireland about 1300 <sc>b. c.</sc>; or pertaining to the descendants of
King Milesius; hence, Irish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Milesian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Milesian
<hw>Mi*le"sian</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A native or
inhabitant of Miletus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A native or inhabitant of Ireland.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Milestone</ent>⟦br⟧
